                     These are the words directly spelled out from out master Sri Anandha Agasta. 

                     Exactly one year ago on may 2019, I was always living an awakened blissful life, spending a large part of the time with the kids, healthy life process with similar vibrating souls at other times, joy, dance, celebrations, music, loving Nature, poetry. I am called Kumar by beloved parents and Karate Siva by others and Agasta by my Gurus.  

                     Athmakalin Sangama was started for the 7 souls who have been in a long day connected with me, who were ready to live and die with us along with my wife. The aim is, for the souls to live together in a blissful healthy way in one place, attain the enlightenment which is the noble purpose of life and to reach the state of Samadhi known as Arhant in one place altogether. 

                     The training for this called Karma Yoga started 7 months ago when I have decided to squeeze out the essence of the spiritual Knowledge, I had learned from wandering around for 20 years and give it to those 7 souls in 2 years. Karma yoga is the act of doing for God or any of the activities given by the Guru with full involvement (devotee) and without any attachment, any expectation. Because when you do a karma with an expectation there comes an attachment to that expectation. That attachment is the cause of all your karma. It can cause fluctuations in your involvement. It was decided to conduct this Karma Yoga practice in 4 phases. Making 100 YouTube VDOs, Website Designing, 500 articles in the first phase. And deciding to prepare the living space for the samadhi. Karma Yogas: Divided according to the qualifications of the 7 souls and thier lifestyle and skills. 35 other souls with similar frequencies have joined to help them harmonize.  

                     With that their ego also began to show its head out. Some souls were ready to be cut off while some souls were ambushed as they prepared to escape. Some are Fearful. Some attacked as well. In the midst of this the exercises for everyone like Atma Sutra, Atma Tantra, Atma Satori, Atma Vipassana and so on continues. Atma Paravasa and Atma Samadhi were not given due to lack of qualified souls for it. Preliminary work on Karma Yoga continued. Misunderstood souls parted. Unworthy souls were expelled. Realized souls re-entered. The task of quietly Witnessing everyone continued. Today (19 Sept- 2020) the first step of Karma Yoga is completed after 7 months. Among the tasks given, an additional 250 quotations also are made by the standing committee as part of their karma yoga Out of a total of 42 souls, 5 souls are finally qualified as Karma Yogis in the first phase, out of 7 souls who have invested their own problems and selfishness and missed out on Karma Yoga. The next 3 phases of Karma Yoga training will be started for them. It is through this karma yoga that our knowledge expands and we are able to realize the enlightenment and able to work towards it. Our qualities are getting superior. We are able to travel continuously in a positive way towards our goal of full awakening with the same mindfulness. 
                     and Hence continue to do the karma yoga with full awareness without any expectation or attachment to prepare for the next phase of karma yoga. The Karma Yoga stages for them will continue till January 16, 2022. At the same time soul trainings will be continued along with spiritual training for themselves. In the coming days Atma Uluji, Atma Tibetan Yoga First Level, Second Level and Atma Psychic Primary, Second Level, also the exclusive exercises for themselves will continue. Wisdom does not come with the knowledge of the brain. And it is not something that can be obtained by keeping only the love of the heart. Love will set a path. That is all. Even Buddha has trained Vipassana in 536 births to attain Enlightenment. After that he has given us some methods and trainings with his experience to achieve Awakening easily. Awakening is something that is known to our knowledge only, bringing it to experience is not such a trivial matter. It’s like an alchemy. Karma: Play a very important role here in preventing awakening. Hence, we have to attain some sidhis like seeing our past and future life and few more exercises helps in easily destroying our karma. So, you can't progress without throwing your knowledge in the trash. What we want to achieve is something Non - Existential! Something that can never be achieved ...? This is a journey aimed at something that is not in the destination ...! Our journey is like a blind man traveling with a lamp in his hand. The only thing here which is our companion is Perseverance that too is like that lamp with the blind man. Our aim is to attain the state of awakening called enlightenment and thereby attain the state of salvation called ArahantAll live happily together in the same place with awareness and attain samadhi. As far as our intellect knows Bliss with Awakening is the supremacy of life. Sri Sri, These are the words of Bodhi Satva. 
