 his own economic needs. So, he asks to buy a bag of candy to his friend from Namakkal,they will get one candy in return. A bag of candy is one rupee 80 paise. If he sells it, he will get a profit of twenty paisa. His friend Mani, a student, buys a bag of candy and gives it to him. Mani is currently a pastor in a Christian church. He had the self-confidence to fulfill his economic need at an early age. During the Pongal festival, he conducted sports competitions such as skating, tug-of-war, bicycle racing, and running. Also he involved in things like screening movies during the Mari Amman festival. He also conducted kabaddi competitions. During that time, his team announced that the prize money was ten thousand and one and held kabaddi competitions. By the time he finished ninth grade, his friend Senthil had gone to another side to learn karate. On his advice,  Siva Master also went to Sensai P.K.U. Kanth and started learning the art of karate. But his father did not allow it and said you have already learnt two belts and it is enough. He also denied that he could pay the fee of six rupees a month.  

